"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Husky v9 Hook Compatibility\n\n## Context\n\nPR #355 fixed hook installation to use `git rev-parse --git-path hooks`, which correctly resolves `core.hooksPath`. When Husky is present, this resolves to `.husky/_/`. However, Husky regenerates `.husky/_/` on every `npm install` (via `prepare: \"husky\"` in package.json), wiping Entire's hooks.\n\n**The fix**: When Husky is detected, inject Entire's commands into the **user-facing** `.husky/<hookname>` files instead of writing standalone hooks into `.husky/_/`. User-facing files are committed to the repo and survive `npm install`.\n\nCloses #228.\n\n## How Husky v9 Works\n\n```\n.husky/\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ _/                  ‚Üê generated wrappers (gitignored, regenerated on npm install)\n‚îÇ                         core.hooksPath points here\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ pre-commit          ‚Üê user-editable, committed, survives npm install\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ prepare-commit-msg  ‚Üê user-editable, committed, survives npm install\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ ...\n```\n\nGit calls `.husky/_/<hook>` (wrapper) which delegates to `.husky/<hook>` (user script).\n\n## Changes\n\n**Single file modified**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/hooks.go`\n**Single test file modified**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/hooks_test.go`\n\n### 1. Husky Detection\n\nAdd helpers to detect if `core.hooksPath` resolves to a Husky-managed directory:\n\n- `isHuskyHooksPath(hooksDir string) bool` ‚Äî checks if path ends in `.husky/_`\n- `getHuskyUserHooksDir(hooksDir string) string` ‚Äî returns `.husky/` parent dir (or empty)\n\nDetection: path pattern match (`.husky/_`) + verify `.husky/` directory exists on disk.\n\n### 2. Injection Content\n\nAdd `buildHuskyInjectionSpecs(cmdPrefix)` returning hook commands wrapped in markers:\n\n```sh\n# BEGIN entire\n# Entire CLI hooks\nentire hooks git prepare-commit-msg \"$1\" \"$2\" 2>/dev/null || true\n# END entire\n```\n\nNo shebang needed ‚Äî Husky v9 user scripts run in the wrapper's shell context.\n\n### 3. Modified `InstallGitHook()`\n\nExtract existing logic into `installStandardHooks()`. Add branch:\n\n```\nInstallGitHook()\n‚îú‚îÄ GetHooksDir() ‚Üí resolves core.hooksPath\n‚îú‚îÄ if isHuskyHooksPath(hooksDir) && .husky/ exists:\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ installHuskyHooks() ‚Äî inject into .husky/<hookname>\n‚îÇ      ‚îî‚îÄ also clean up any stale standalone hooks in .husky/_/\n‚îî‚îÄ else:\n    ‚îî‚îÄ installStandardHooks() ‚Äî existing behavior\n```\n\n`installHuskyHooks()` uses `injectHuskyHookContent()` which:\n- Creates new `.husky/<hookname>` if it doesn't exist\n- Appends `# BEGIN entire` block to existing files\n- Replaces existing block if already present (idempotent)\n\n### 4. Modified `isGitHookInstalledInHooksDir()`\n\nWhen Husky is detected, check `.husky/<hookname>` files for the `# BEGIN entire` marker instead of checking `.husky/_/<hookname>`.\n\n### 5. Modified `RemoveGitHook()`\n\nExtract existing logic into `removeStandardHooks()`. Add Husky branch that strips `# BEGIN entire` / `# END entire` blocks from `.husky/<hookname>` files. If the file becomes empty after removal, delete it.\n\n### 6. Block Manipulation Helpers\n\n- `extractEntireBlock(content) string` ‚Äî returns text between BEGIN/END markers (inclusive)\n- `replaceEntireBlock(content, newBlock) string` ‚Äî replaces the marker-wrapped block\n\n### Edge Cases\n\n| Scenario | Behavior |\n|----------|----------|\n| `entire enable` before `husky init` | `.husky/` doesn't exist, falls back to standard install in `.husky/_/` |\n| User removes Husky later | `core.hooksPath` reverts, standard path used; stale blocks in `.husky/` are inert |\n| Already has Entire block | `extractEntireBlock` detects it, replaces with current version |\n| Stale hooks in `.husky/_/` from PR #355 | `installHuskyHooks()` cleans them up to prevent double execution |\n| Worktrees with Husky | `.husky/` is part of the repo, shared across worktrees ‚Äî works correctly |\n\n## Tests\n\n**Unit tests** in `hooks_test.go`:\n- `TestIsHuskyHooksPath` ‚Äî detection with various path patterns\n- `TestGetHuskyUserHooksDir` ‚Äî derives `.husky/` from `.husky/_`\n- `TestInstallGitHook_HuskyDetected` ‚Äî injects into `.husky/<hookname>`, not `.husky/_/`\n- `TestInstallGitHook_HuskyIdempotent` ‚Äî second install returns 0\n- `TestInstallGitHook_HuskyExistingContent` ‚Äî preserves user content, appends block\n- `TestInstallGitHook_HuskyUpdateBlock` ‚Äî replaces existing block on re-install\n- `TestRemoveGitHook_Husky` ‚Äî strips blocks, removes empty files\n- `TestRemoveGitHook_HuskyPreservesUserContent` ‚Äî user content survives removal\n- `TestIsGitHookInstalled_Husky` ‚Äî detection works with injected blocks\n- `TestInstallGitHook_HuskyDirNotExists` ‚Äî falls back to standard install\n- `TestInstallGitHook_HuskyCleansUpGenerated` ‚Äî removes stale `.husky/_/` hooks\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\n```\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/robin/.REDACTED.jsonl\n\n---\n\n<task-notification>\n<task-id>aa827eb</task-id>\n<status>failed</status>\n<summary>Agent \"Design Husky hook compat plan\" failed: classifyHandoffIfNeeded is not defined</summary>\n</task-notification>\nFull transcript available at: /private/tmp/claude-501/-Users-robin-Developer-cli/tasks/aa827eb.output\n\n---\n\ncommit and push this, and raise a draft PR"